Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of Ondo State Development and Investment Promotion Agency (ONDIPA) Mr. Boye Oyewumi, has declared his intention to run in next year’s general election. Oyewumi, an investment and development expert, said he is running to represent Ondo South Senatorial District in the National Assembly. The former Special Adviser on Investment and Development to Governor Rotimi Akeredolu and hails from the ancient town of Oke-Igbo in Ile Oluji/Okeigbo Local Government Area spoke at the weekend at a consultative meeting with the leadership of All Progressives Congress (APC) in his locality.   Supreme Court fixes judgment for May 6 in Rivers, Imo…     Why Igboho’s detention was extended, by lawyer     Our position on Igboho, Kanu, Abba Kyari, by Malami   Oyewumi promised to use the instrumentalities of legislation to revolutionise the investment drives of the Nigerian Government and to lobby for the agenda of Ondo-State Government on Job Creations through industrialisation. - Advertisement - He said, “My dear fathers, mothers and leaders, I am here today to seek your blessing and a go-ahead to join the democratic challenge for the representative of our Senatorial seat in National Assembly in 2023. “Let me say very expressly that I am intellectually, mentally, emotionally and physically prepared for this struggle for the restructuring of our nationhood, and I want you to boost my morale with your endorsement as I matched on”, Oyewumi said. Chairman of APC in Okeigbo Zone, Mr Samson Ojetayo, described Oyewumi as a man who loves to help others. He expressed confidence that Oyewumi would impact the lives of his senatorial constituents even beyond his promises if elected to serve as a Senator.